<p>If you want a simpler way to conceptualize how this works, just remember the following.</p>
<ol>
	<li>More support for criterion = proposal scores affected more by this criterion</li>
	<li>More objection for criterion = proposal scores affected less by this criterion</li>
	<li>More objections overall = lower score potential for any proposal</li>
</ol>

<p>Proposals are ranked by how high they score. This score is meant as an estimate of how much support a proposal will have, so as to identify which ones to propose first. It is not designed to provide a definitive decision. To find out if a group is comfortable going with a proposal, you have to ask directly.</p>

